data.reddit:
Age: 26
Sex: Female
Height: 5”8
Weight: 171lbs
Race: White
Duration of complaint: On and off for around 7 months or more. 
Location: England || bladder
Existing medical issues: Severe depression and anxiety, not currently on any medication. 

Quite a few months ago around the beginning of this year I got what I thought was a UTI, the first time I’ve ever had one. There was no pain or burning sensation when I pee’d, I just couldn’t fully empty my bladder and my urine had an odd odour. Stupidly I thought it would just go away on its own and since I wasn’t in pain, I didn’t bother going to the doctor. Eventually it did stop after a week. 

But then about a month later or so it came back and it was really frustrating and uncomfortable to constantly feel the urge to pee, so I did go to a doctor but because it’s the first time going to the doctor with this kind of thing, I didn’t know I needed to take a sample first before the appointment and instead of being understanding, my doctor made me feel stupid and embarrassed. So I left and didn’t feel like going back at all. 

Now months later, after this issue constantly going away for a month or more then coming back for a few weeks, I’m concerned and incredibly frustrated. Is this a recurring UTI due to it not being treated the first time? Or could it be another medical issue?

The symptoms are always the same, there’s no pain and no burning sensation. I just can’t empty my bladder and have a very short interrupted stream, sometimes my urine will have a weird “smokey” odour. I also constantly feel like I need to pee, even after I’ve just gone. I’m definitely planning on going back to the doctor but it can take a month to wait for an appointment at my surgery.
